<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="547" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,681,1242,1264]" box="[151,681,1242,1264]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">
<taxonomicName authority="Barrois &amp; Moniez, 1887" authorityName="Barrois &amp; Moniez" authorityYear="1887" box="[151,560,1242,1264]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Tiphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koenikei">
<emphasis box="[151,307,1242,1264]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">Tiphys koenikei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barrois" box="[314,560,1242,1264]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" refString="Barrois, T. &amp; Moniez, R. (1887) Catalogue des Hydrachnides recueilles dans le nord de la France avec des notes critiques et la description d`especes nouvelles. Bigot Freres, Lille, 36 pp." type="book" year="1887">
Barrois &amp; Moniez, 
<number box="[511,560,1242,1264]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="1887.0">1887</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
— 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[587,681,1243,1264]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">nov. syn.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1309,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">
<taxonomicName box="[151,335,1309,1333]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koenikei">
<emphasis box="[151,335,1309,1333]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">Forelia koenikei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a little reported species, illustrated only by 
<bibRefCitation author="Besseling" box="[862,1057,1309,1334]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" refString="Besseling, A. J. (1964) De Nederlandse Watermijten (Hydrachnellae Latreille, 1802). Monographieen van de Nederlandsche Entomologische Vereeniging, 1, 1 - 199." type="journal article" year="1964">
Besseling (
<number box="[987,1048,1309,1334]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In the original description of the species, 
<bibRefCitation author="Barrois" box="[246,533,1345,1370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" refString="Barrois, T. &amp; Moniez, R. (1887) Catalogue des Hydrachnides recueilles dans le nord de la France avec des notes critiques et la description d`especes nouvelles. Bigot Freres, Lille, 36 pp." type="book" year="1887">
Barrois &amp; Moniez (
<number box="[467,525,1346,1370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="1887.0">1887</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that it is close to 
<taxonomicName box="[807,952,1346,1369]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegator">
<emphasis box="[807,952,1346,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">F. variegator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, they compared the species only with 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller, 1776" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1776" box="[210,504,1381,1406]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liliacea">
<emphasis box="[210,325,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">F. liliacea</emphasis>
(Müller, 
<number box="[436,496,1381,1406]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="1776.0">1776</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[518,704,1381,1405]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koenikei">
<emphasis box="[518,704,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">Forelia koenikei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by an elongate dorsal shield, while the ventral shield has secondary sclerotization encompassing the genital plates and the excretory pore. IV-leg- 
<number box="[1270,1283,1417,1442]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="6.0">6</number>
has ventrally three heavy, curved setae. All these characters apply also to 
<taxonomicName box="[839,985,1454,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegator">
<emphasis box="[839,985,1454,1477]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">F. variegator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although IV-leg- 
<number box="[1188,1201,1453,1478]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="6.0">6</number>
has only two heavy, curved setae. But according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Besseling" box="[507,700,1489,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" refString="Besseling, A. J. (1964) De Nederlandse Watermijten (Hydrachnellae Latreille, 1802). Monographieen van de Nederlandsche Entomologische Vereeniging, 1, 1 - 199." type="journal article" year="1964">
Besseling (
<number box="[633,691,1489,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
IV-leg- 
<number box="[790,803,1489,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="6.0">6</number>
has 
<number box="[857,872,1490,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<number box="[882,895,1490,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" value="3.0">3</number>
) heavy, curved setae. Therefore we consider 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koenikei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">F. koenikei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,629,1526,1549]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Forelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegator">
<emphasis box="[484,629,1526,1549]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="547">F. variegator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
